            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1210" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1210">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Italy)/7–2945: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1210<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-29">July 29
                            [1945.]</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>155.…<note n="1" xml:id="d1210fn1">Here follows a summary of <ref target="#d1207">document No. 1207</ref> and its enclosure.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Department has discussed Yugo note (Belgrade’s 296)<note n="2" xml:id="d1210fn2">The Embassy’s telegram is not printed. For the text of the Yugoslav note
                        referred to, see the enclosure to <ref target="#d1207">document No.
                            1207</ref>.</note> with British and is now awaiting receipt their views
                    before instructing Embassy Belgrade re reply.</p>
                <pb facs="1419" n="1221" xml:id="pg_1221"/>
                <p>We expect that local elections will be held in Venezia Giulia as in other <gloss target="#t_AMG1">AMG</gloss> territory at approximately same time such
                    elections are held in other parts of Italy and <gloss target="#t_AMG1">AMG</gloss> has already initiated certain preparations to that end.
                    Department however agrees with view set forth in final paragraph Belgrade’s
                        318<note n="3" xml:id="d1210fn3">
                        <ref target="#d1209">Document No. 1209</ref>.</note> that to accept Yugo
                    thesis that area is liberated territory (i. e. Yugo liberated territory) would
                    in effect prejudge final question of sovereignty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
